**Lemma 2**.: _We define the equivalence relation \(\sim\) on \(\mathrm{St}(k,D)\) to be \(\bm{Y}_{1}\sim\bm{Y}_{2}\) whenever (70) is satisfied with respect to \(\bm{Y}_{1},\bm{Y}_{2}\in\mathrm{St}(k,D)\). The fact that a binary relation is an equivalence relation \(\sim\) implies that the following three statements hold for \({}^{\forall}\bm{Y}_{1},\bm{Y}_{2},\bm{Y}_{3}\in\mathrm{St}(k,D)\)._

**Reflexivity**: \(\bm{Y}_{1}\sim\bm{Y}_{1}\).
**Symmetry**: \(\bm{Y}_{1}\sim\bm{Y}_{2}\Rightarrow\bm{Y}_{2}\sim\bm{Y}_{1}\).
**Transitivity**: \(\bm{Y}_{1}\sim\bm{Y}_{2}\wedge\bm{Y}_{2}\sim\bm{Y}_{3}\Rightarrow\bm{Y}_{1} \sim\bm{Y}_{3}\).

